name_to_write_changer <- function(names,old, new){
  id <- which(names == old)
  if(length(id) > 0){
    if(length(id) == 1){
      names[id] <- new
    }else{
      print("Error1")
    }
  }
  return(names)
}
rarefy_i <- function(otu_table,sample,rarefy_i = T){ #rownames must be taxonomy, samples in columns, only count values.
  if(rarefy_i){
  otu_table$taxonomy <- rownames(otu_table)
  otu_table <- RAM::OTU.rarefy(data = list(data = otu_table),sample = sample)
  otu_table <- otu_table$data
  otu_table <- otu_table[,-ncol(otu_table)]
  return(otu_table)
  }else{
    return(otu_table)
  }
}
tie_breaker <- function(otu_table, tie_breaking = T){ #must only contain counts 0,1,2,...
  if(tie_breaking) {noise_mat <- matrix(data = runif(n = nrow(otu_table)*ncol(otu_table),
                        min = -0.001,max = 0.001),
                        nrow = nrow(otu_table),
                        ncol = ncol(otu_table))
  }else{
    noise_mat <- matrix(data = 0,nrow = nrow(otu_table),ncol = ncol(otu_table))
  }
  return(otu_table + noise_mat)
}
permutator <- function(otu_table, permute = T){
  if(permute){
    return( matrix(nrow = nrow(otu_table),data = sample(x = as.numeric(as.matrix(otu_table)),replace = F)) )
  }else{
    return(otu_table)
  }
}
boot_strapper <- function(otu_table, boot_strap = T){
  if(boot_strap){
    ids <- sample(x = 1:ncol(otu_table),size = ncol(otu_table),replace = T)
    return(otu_table[,ids])
  }else{
    return(otu_table)
  }
}

4 minimum threshold

This part computes the minimum threshold.

fname_threshold <- paste("data/co_oc_res/",group,cvdstatus,initial_iter,p_iter_big,".Rdata",sep="_")
if(!file.exists(fname_threshold)){
threshold <- c()
maxtr <- c()
for(p_iter_big in 1:initial_perm){
  cat(p_iter_big, "\n")
otu_table <- permutator(otu_table = otu_table,permute = T)

time1 <- Sys.time()

cora2 <- cora_min <- cora_max <- cora

  cat(r_iter, "|")
  otu_table_r <- rarefy_i(otu_table = otu_table,sample = min(colSums(otu_table)),rarefy_i = T)
  for(bo_iter in 1:boot_iter){
      otu_a_rb <- boot_strapper(otu_table = otu_table_r[,groupa],boot_strap = T)
      for(no_iter in 1:noise_iter){
        #permutation
        otu_a_rbp  <- permutator(otu_table = otu_a_rb,permute = F) #############
        otu_a_rbpn <- tie_breaker(otu_table = otu_a_rbp,tie_breaking = T)
        boot_cor_a <- cor(t(otu_a_rbpn),method = met)
        cora <- cora + boot_cor_a
        cora2 <- cora2 + boot_cor_a^2
        rownames(boot_cor_a) <- colnames(boot_cor_a) <- NULL
      
        iter_id <- bo_iter  +  boot_iter*(no_iter-1)  + noise_iter*boot_iter*(r_iter-1)
        cora_array[,,iter_id] <- boot_cor_a
    }
  }
}
cor.res <- cora/iter

8 prepare OTU names to write on plots

#taxonomy
taxonomy <- rownames(otu_table)
taxonomy <- (strsplit(x = taxonomy,split = ";"))
taxa <- c()
for(i in 1:length(taxonomy)){
  taxa <- rbind(taxa, taxonomy[[i]])
}
taxa[which((taxa[,6] == "g__Clostridium") & taxa[,5] == "f__Erysipelotrichaceae"),6] <- gsub(pattern = "g__Clostridium",replacement = "g__Erysipelatoclostridium",x = taxa[which(taxa[,6] == "g__Clostridium")[2],6])
name_to_write <- c()
for(i in 1:nrow(taxa)){
  last <- T
  j <- ncol(taxa)
  if(is.na(taxa[i,j])){
    res <- "   "
  }else{
    
  while(last){
    if((taxa[i,j] == "Other") | (substr(taxa[i,j],start = 2,stop = nchar(taxa[i,j])) == "__")){
      j <- j-1
    }else{
      last <- F
    }
  }
  res <- paste(taxa[i,j:(min(j+1,ncol(taxa)))],sep = "",collapse = ";")
  if(substr(res,start = 2,stop = 3) == "__") res <- substr(res,start = 4,stop = nchar(res))
  }
  res <- gsub(pattern = "__",replacement = '_',x = res)
  name_to_write <- c(name_to_write, res)
}

corana.n.ordered <- corana.n[hcl$order,hcl$order]

zs <- sapply(X = 1:240, function(i) length(which(otu_table_r[i,groupn] == 0)))

for(qi in 1:5){
  hv <- sapply(X = 1:240, function(i) quantile((corana.n[i,-i]),na.rm = T)[qi])
  points(zs,hv, col = scales::alpha(coll[qi],0.5),pch = 19)  
}
abline(h = 0,col = "gray")
legend("bottomright",legend = names(quantile(1)),col = coll,pch = 19)
